    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-06T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="858"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d858">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/397: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-07T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 7, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received December 7—11:27
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1009. 1. My British and German colleagues and I have decided that, barring some
                    developments which may precipitate our action, Embassy staffs including
                    ourselves will go aboard our ships tomorrow evening, returning ashore next day
                    if that is feasible. (Our Italian <pb facs="0779" n="772" xml:id="pg_772"/>
                    colleague, is as reported, already aboard the U.S.S. <hi rend="italic"
                        >Panay</hi>.) We are not informing the press until we actually leave.
                    Tomorrow we shall inform the Chinese authorities that we are sleeping aboard but
                    expect to be at our offices during daytime.</p>
                <p>2. Repeated to Hankow, Peiping, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
